-- FRAME 0: evaluate seed (identity cell)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Ready set: { seed } — given premise ≡ "A space station..." already bound
-- Blocked: everything else

⊢ seed
  given premise ≡ "A space station in the year 3000 — humanity's last outpost after Earth became uninhabitable. Population: ~50,000. Orbiting a gas giant in the Tau Ceti system, 12 light-years from Earth."
  yield premise

-- eval-one: seed is an identity cell — premise is already bound via ≡.
-- yield premise ≡ given premise. No LLM needed.

  yield premise ≡ "A space station in the year 3000 — humanity's last outpost after Earth became uninhabitable. Population: ~50,000. Orbiting a gas giant in the Tau Ceti system, 12 light-years from Earth."

-- oracle checks:
