-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- FRAME 1: evaluate geography (soft cell, LLM) [iteration 0]
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Ready set: { geography, history, culture } — picking geography first
-- geography's inputs:
--   seed→premise ≡ "A space station in the year 3000..."
--   history→backstory ≡ ⊥ (given? tolerates this)
--   culture→customs ≡ ⊥ (given? tolerates this)

⊢ geography
  given seed→premise ≡ "A space station in the year 3000 — humanity's last outpost after Earth became uninhabitable. Population: ~50,000. Orbiting a gas giant in the Tau Ceti system, 12 light-years from Earth."
  given? history→backstory ≡ ⊥
  given? culture→customs ≡ ⊥
  yield layout, sectors[], environment

  ∴ Design the physical layout of the space station described in «seed→premise».
    If «history→backstory» is available (not ⊥), consider the backstory...
    If peer outputs are ⊥, design freely from the premise alone.

-- LLM evaluation (peer outputs are ⊥ — designing freely from premise):

  yield layout ≡ "The Tau Ceti Ark is a rotating O'Neill cylinder, 8 km long and 2 km in diameter. The station spins at 0.5 RPM to produce 0.85g along the inner surface. The cylinder is divided into six longitudinal strips alternating between habitation and window bands. A non-rotating central spine houses the docking hub, zero-g manufacturing, and the primary fusion reactor array. Two endcaps: the Forward Cap (facing the gas giant Aurelius) houses observation decks and the navigation array; the Aft Cap contains the propulsion remnants and deep storage vaults."

  yield sectors ≡ [
    { name: "The Greenway", purpose: "Agricultural and park strip — hydroponic farms, orchards, and the station's only open sky. Runs the full 8 km length." },
    { name: "Midtown", purpose: "Primary residential and commercial sector. Tiered hab-blocks from cylinder floor to 200m elevation. Population density: ~15,000." },
    { name: "The Spine", purpose: "Zero-g central axis. Docking bays, cargo handling, zero-g manufacturing, and the fusion reactor array. Access via six radial elevators." },
    { name: "Old Foundation", purpose: "Original construction sector, now mixed industrial and low-income housing. Contains the oldest structures on the station, some dating to initial assembly." },
    { name: "The Ringworks", purpose: "Engineering and life-support sector. Water recycling, atmospheric processors, waste reclamation. Wraps the aft endcap." },
    { name: "Aurelius View", purpose: "Forward observation and science sector. Telescopes, planetary science labs, the Council Chamber with a panoramic viewport facing the gas giant." }
  ]

  yield environment ≡ "Life support: closed-loop atmospheric recycling (N2/O2 78/21 mix), CO2 scrubbers in The Ringworks with biological backup in The Greenway. Water: 95% reclamation rate via distillation cascades, supplemented by ice mining from Aurelius's ring system. Gravity: centripetal via rotation at 0.85g on the inner surface, zero-g in The Spine. Power: twin deuterium-helium-3 fusion reactors in The Spine, backup solar collectors on the window bands. Emergency: each sector can seal independently; 72-hour independent life support per sector."

-- oracle checks (aspirational under ⊢∘ co-evolve):
--   ⊨ layout describes overall structure with dimensions → ✓
--     O'Neill cylinder, 8 km × 2 km, 0.5 RPM, 0.85g, dual endcaps
--   ⊨ length(sectors) ≥ 4 → ✓ (6 sectors)
--   ⊨ environment addresses life support systems → ✓
--     air, water, gravity, power, emergency all covered

-- state after frame 1: geography frozen (iteration 0, tentative).
