-- FRAME 3: evaluate culture (soft cell, LLM) [iteration 0]
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Ready set: { culture }
-- culture's inputs:
--   seed→premise ≡ "A space station in the year 3000..."
--   geography→layout ≡ ⊥
--   history→backstory ≡ ⊥

⊢ culture
  given seed→premise ≡ "A space station in the year 3000 — humanity's last outpost after Earth became uninhabitable. Population: ~50,000. Orbiting a gas giant in the Tau Ceti system, 12 light-years from Earth."
  given? geography→layout ≡ ⊥
  given? history→backstory ≡ ⊥
  yield customs, social-structure, traditions[], taboos[]

  ∴ Design the culture of the space station in «seed→premise».
    If «geography→layout» is available (not ⊥), reflect physical constraints...
    If peer outputs are ⊥, design freely from the premise alone.

-- LLM evaluation (peer outputs are ⊥ — designing freely):

  yield customs ≡ "Life on the station is governed by radical resource consciousness. Every citizen tracks their personal resource budget — water, air processing share, caloric allocation — via wrist-mounted 'life ledgers.' Waste is socially unacceptable; repair culture dominates. Objects are inherited, repurposed, never discarded. Greetings include the phrase 'breathe easy' — an acknowledgment that the air you share is finite. Meals are communal by default; private eating is reserved for mourning or illness. Music is the dominant art form because it requires no physical materials."

  yield social-structure ≡ "Governance: the Council of Seven — one elected representative per major station zone, plus a rotating Chancellor drawn by lottery from the general population. The lottery system prevents dynasty formation. Below the Council: Guild system organized by function (Engineers, Growers, Medics, Teachers, Recyclers, Navigators, Keepers). Guild membership is by aptitude and choice, not birth. Social mobility is high — Guild transfers happen every 5 years during Reallocation. Class distinctions exist informally: Spine workers (zero-g laborers) are both respected for toughness and pitied for health risks."

  yield traditions ≡ [
    { name: "Day of Silence", description: "Annual observance marking the loss of contact with Earth. All non-essential systems are dimmed. Citizens gather in sector commons to share stories of Earth passed down through generations. No work is performed." },
    { name: "The Breathing", description: "Monthly ceremony where atmospheric processors are briefly made audible throughout the station. Citizens pause and listen to the sound of their shared air being cleaned. A reminder of mutual dependence." },
    { name: "First Light", description: "Coming-of-age ceremony at age 16. The young person spends 24 hours alone in the observation deck facing Aurelius, contemplating their place in the station's future. They return to announce their chosen Guild." },
    { name: "Reallocation", description: "Every 5 years, citizens may change Guilds, residences, or sector assignments. A festival atmosphere — part job fair, part community celebration. Prevents social calcification." }
  ]

  yield taboos ≡ [
    { name: "Waste Hoarding", description: "Keeping broken items without repair intent. Hoarding strains recycling systems and is considered a form of theft from the community." },
    { name: "Sealed Doors", description: "Locking personal quarters against neighbors without Council authorization. In emergencies, sealed doors kill. The Midway Mutiny began when a faction sealed the bridge. Locked doors symbolize betrayal of communal trust." },
    { name: "Birth Overrun", description: "Having children beyond one's allocation without Council dispensation. Population is the station's most critical resource constraint. Unauthorized births trigger immediate resource rebalancing across the offender's entire sector." }
  ]

-- oracle checks (aspirational under ⊢∘ co-evolve):
--   ⊨ social-structure describes governance → ✓ (Council of Seven, lottery Chancellor, Guild system)
--   ⊨ length(traditions) ≥ 3 → ✓ (4 traditions)
--   ⊨ length(taboos) ≥ 2 → ✓ (3 taboos)
--   ⊨ customs reflect life in an enclosed space environment → ✓
--     Resource budgets, communal meals, air consciousness, repair culture

-- state after frame 3: culture frozen (iteration 0, tentative).
