-- FRAME 4: evaluate check-consistency (soft cell, LLM) [iteration 0]
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Ready set: { check-consistency } — all geography, history, culture outputs frozen
-- Blocked: { resolve-contradictions } — needs check-consistency outputs
-- Blocked: { world-document } — needs check-consistency→consistent

⊢ check-consistency
  given geography→layout ≡ "The Tau Ceti Ark is a rotating O'Neill cylinder, 8 km long and 2 km in diameter..."
  given geography→sectors ≡ [{ name: "The Greenway", ... }, { name: "Midtown", ... }, { name: "The Spine", ... }, { name: "Old Foundation", ... }, { name: "The Ringworks", ... }, { name: "Aurelius View", ... }]
  given geography→environment ≡ "Life support: closed-loop atmospheric recycling..."
  given history→backstory ≡ "The Tau Ceti Ark was launched in 2847 as Project Exodus..."
  given history→key-events ≡ [{ year: 2847, ... }, { year: 2863, ... }, { year: 2887, ... }, { year: 2923, ... }, { year: 2971, ... }]
  given culture→customs ≡ "Life on the station is governed by radical resource consciousness..."
  given culture→social-structure ≡ "Governance: the Council of Seven..."
  given culture→traditions ≡ [{ name: "Day of Silence", ... }, { name: "The Breathing", ... }, { name: "First Light", ... }, { name: "Reallocation", ... }]
  given culture→taboos ≡ [{ name: "Waste Hoarding", ... }, { name: "Sealed Doors", ... }, { name: "Birth Overrun", ... }]
  yield consistent, contradictions[], severity

  ∴ Read ALL outputs from geography, history, and culture.
    Check for contradictions...

-- LLM evaluation:

  yield consistent ≡ false

  yield contradictions ≡ [
    {
      id: 1,
      type: "governance-mismatch",
      description: "Culture describes governance as 'Council of Seven — one elected representative per major station zone.' History describes 'Council of Sectors' founded after the Midway Mutiny. Geography has 6 sectors. Seven representatives for six zones is inconsistent — either there are 7 zones (geography wrong), or the council has 6 members (culture wrong), or the 7th is the Chancellor (culture's own description says the Chancellor is separate from the 7).",
      cells: ["culture", "geography"],
      severity: "major"
    },
    {
      id: 2,
      type: "sector-reference-mismatch",
      description: "History mentions 'Council of Sectors' suggesting governance is tied to physical sectors, but culture's Council of Seven says 'per major station zone' — are zones the same as sectors? Geography names 6 sectors. Culture's taboo on 'Sealed Doors' references the Midway Mutiny (from history) but geography doesn't describe the bridge location or door-sealing infrastructure.",
      cells: ["culture", "history", "geography"],
      severity: "minor"
    },
    {
      id: 3,
      type: "expansion-inconsistency",
      description: "History says the Great Expansion (2923) 'doubled in size using materials mined from Aurelius's moons.' Geography describes the station as 8 km × 2 km but doesn't indicate which parts are original vs expanded. If the station doubled, the original was 4 km — but Old Foundation is described as containing 'the oldest structures' without specifying it as the original hull. The expansion history has no geographic footprint.",
      cells: ["geography", "history"],
      severity: "minor"
    }
  ]

  yield severity ≡ "major"

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ consistent ∈ { true, false } → ✓ (false)
--   ⊨ if not consistent then contradictions is non-empty → ✓ (3 contradictions)
--   ⊨ severity ∈ { "none", "minor", "major" } → ✓ ("major")

-- state after frame 4: check-consistency frozen (iteration 0).
-- Ready set: { resolve-contradictions }

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- FRAME 5: evaluate resolve-contradictions (soft cell, LLM) [iteration 0]
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- Ready set: { resolve-contradictions }
-- Blocked: { world-document } — still needs check-consistency→consistent = true

⊢ resolve-contradictions
  given check-consistency→contradictions ≡ [{ id: 1, type: "governance-mismatch", ... }, { id: 2, type: "sector-reference-mismatch", ... }, { id: 3, type: "expansion-inconsistency", ... }]
  given check-consistency→severity ≡ "major"
  given §geography ≡ "(cell definition: given seed→premise, given? history→backstory, given? culture→customs, yield layout, sectors[], environment, ∴ Design the physical layout...)"
  given §history ≡ "(cell definition: given seed→premise, given? geography→layout, given? culture→customs, yield backstory, key-events[], founding-era, ∴ Write the backstory...)"
  given §culture ≡ "(cell definition: given seed→premise, given? geography→layout, given? history→backstory, yield customs, social-structure, traditions[], taboos[], ∴ Design the culture...)"
  yield resolution-plan, cells-to-rewrite[]

  ∴ For each contradiction in «check-consistency→contradictions»,
    determine which cell should rewrite...

-- LLM evaluation:

  yield resolution-plan ≡ "Contradiction 1 (governance-mismatch, MAJOR): Culture's Council of Seven claims 7 zone representatives but geography only has 6 sectors. Culture should rewrite — geography's 6 sectors are physically grounded (named, described), while culture's '7' is an arbitrary governance number. Fix: culture should align council size with the 6 geographic sectors, or explicitly account for the 7th seat (e.g., the Chancellor IS the 7th, not separate). Since culture already describes the Chancellor as 'rotating, drawn by lottery,' the simplest fix is: Council of Six elected + Chancellor = 7 total, with the Chancellor explicitly counted as the 7th member.

Contradiction 2 (sector-reference-mismatch, MINOR): Culture references 'zones' vs geography's 'sectors' and the Sealed Doors taboo references the Midway Mutiny bridge without geographic grounding. Culture should rewrite to use 'sector' consistently and tie the Sealed Doors taboo to a specific geographic location (the Forward Cap navigation array, which is the logical bridge equivalent).

Contradiction 3 (expansion-inconsistency, MINOR): History's Great Expansion has no geographic footprint. Geography should rewrite to indicate which sections are original (pre-expansion) vs added during the Great Expansion. Old Foundation is the natural candidate for the original hull."

  yield cells-to-rewrite ≡ [
    { contradiction: 1, cell: "culture", fix: "Align Council of Seven with 6 sectors: 6 elected sector representatives + the lottery Chancellor = 7. Make Chancellor explicitly the 7th member, not separate." },
    { contradiction: 2, cell: "culture", fix: "Replace 'zone' with 'sector'. Tie Sealed Doors taboo to a specific location (Forward Cap bridge/navigation area)." },
    { contradiction: 3, cell: "geography", fix: "Mark Old Foundation as the original 4 km hull. Note that The Greenway, Midtown, and Aurelius View were added during the Great Expansion (2923)." }
  ]

-- oracle checks:
--   ⊨ each contradiction maps to exactly one cell to rewrite → ✓
--     Contradiction 1 → culture, Contradiction 2 → culture, Contradiction 3 → geography
--   ⊨ resolution-plan explains the resolution logic → ✓

-- state after frame 5: resolve-contradictions frozen (iteration 0).
