-- LLM evaluation (now aware of geography's expansion-era annotations and culture):

  yield backstory ≡ "The Tau Ceti Ark was launched in 2847 as Project Exodus, Earth's final interstellar colonization effort. By 2840, cascading climate collapse and resource wars had reduced Earth's habitable surface to less than 5%. The United Nations Remnant pooled the last planetary reserves to construct and launch the Ark — a 4 km O'Neill cylinder (the 'First Shell') carrying 12,000 colonists plus embryo banks. The 40-year transit to Tau Ceti (2847-2887) tested the colonists' social fabric: the Midway Mutiny of 2863, when a faction demanding return to Earth seized the original bridge in Old Foundation, nearly tore the community apart. 47 died. The event led directly to the founding of the Council of Sectors — distributed governance to prevent any faction from holding absolute power. Upon arrival at Tau Ceti, the plan to terraform Tau Ceti e was abandoned (toxic atmosphere). The colonists chose permanent orbit around the gas giant Aurelius and committed to expanding the station. The Great Expansion (2923) doubled the Ark from 4 km to 8 km, adding The Greenway, Midtown, and Aurelius View using materials mined from Aurelius's moons. The Forward Cap's Council Chamber — with its panoramic view of Aurelius — became the seat of governance, symbolically looking outward rather than back toward Earth. By 2971, the last signal to Earth (sent from Aurelius View's communication array) received no response. The Council declared Earth 'presumed lost.' Today, the station is a self-sustaining civilization of ~50,000, haunted by silence and sustained by discipline."

  yield key-events ≡ [
    { year: 2847, event: "Launch of Project Exodus — 12,000 colonists depart Earth orbit aboard the 4 km First Shell" },
    { year: 2863, event: "The Midway Mutiny — a faction seizes the original bridge in Old Foundation, demanding return to Earth. 47 casualties over 11 days. Leads to founding of the Council of Sectors." },
    { year: 2887, event: "Arrival at Tau Ceti. Survey of Tau Ceti e reveals toxic atmosphere. Decision to remain in permanent orbit around Aurelius." },
    { year: 2923, event: "The Great Expansion — station extended from 4 km to 8 km. The Greenway, Midtown, and Aurelius View constructed using materials from Aurelius's moons. Population reaches 30,000." },
    { year: 2971, event: "The Silence — last signal sent from Aurelius View's communication array to Earth receives no response. Council declares Earth 'presumed lost.' Day of Silence established." }
  ]

  yield founding-era ≡ "The founding era (2847-2890) established the station's core identity. The First Shell — now Old Foundation — was both cradle and crucible. The Midway Mutiny taught that governance must be distributed across sectors, not centralized at a single bridge. This led to the Council of Sectors, where each major section elects a representative. The decision to stay orbital rather than attempt surface colonization created a culture of careful resource management: every gram matters when you cannot resupply from a planet. The founding generation's motto — 'We are what remains' — is inscribed above the Council Chamber in Aurelius View, the seat of governance that didn't exist when the words were first spoken. The motto traveled from Old Foundation's original bridge to the new Council Chamber during the Great Expansion, a physical migration that mirrors the station's growth from survival to permanence."

